<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">286. Ryan, Elaine, with Pam Hait. Color Your Life. San Francisco: StrawberryHill, 1987. Index, bibl., glossary, B/W illus. ISBN 0-89407-085-1. </p><p class="annot">The author, an interior designer, maintains that the readerâ€™sconfidence in their ability to deal with color will improve after completing the included exercises, which range from viewing fruits and vegetables in a supermarket test to identify color preferences, to a review of color taste related to childhood experiences. This popular color psychology book is similar to the many titles for selecting color for personal clothing. Curiously, there are no color illustrations. </p></div>
